\begin{abstract}
Analytic solutions are presented for the hydrodynamic collimation
of a relativistic fireball by a surrounding baryonic wind
emanating from a torus. The opening angle is shown to be
the ratio of the  power output of the inner fireball to that of
the exterior baryonic wind. The gamma ray burst 990123 might thus
be interpreted as a baryon-pure jet with an energy output  of
order  10$^{50}$ erg or less, collimated by a baryonic wind from
a torus with an energy output of order $10^{52}$ erg.
\end{abstract}
